{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"3365a807bdf2a8f2bdf798e1113b751a4f6f8b56"},"timestamp":1444409504,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxMTA2OTcxOTQ=","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/Cpanel-JSON-XS/issues/40","origin":"github"},"title":"Booleans do not round-trip with JSON::PP or Mojo::JSON","message":"A boolean from this modules produces `encountered object '1', but neither allow_blessed nor convert_blessed settings are enabled` with `JSON::PP` and a 0/1 with `Mojo::JSON`. Both modules [[1](https://metacpan.org/source/MAKAMAKA/JSON-PP-2.27300/lib/JSON/PP.pm#L416), [2](https://github.com/kraih/mojo/blob/master/lib/Mojo/JSON.pm#L241)] currently use and expect a `JSON::PP::Boolean` blessed scalar reference, while this module produces a `JSON::XS::Boolean`. New versions of `JSON::XS` also [appear to produce a `JSON::PP::Boolean`](https://metacpan.org/source/MLEHMANN/Types-Serialiser-1.0/Serialiser.pm#L105).\n\nExample:\n\n``` perl\nuse v5.16;\n\nuse Cpanel::JSON::XS qw( decode_json );\nuse JSON::PP qw( encode_json );\n\nsay encode_json(decode_json('[true]'));\n```","files":null}]}